    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    C.L.R James writes to Leonard Woolf to inform him he will write a 10,000 word pamphlet and 
                    implores him to publish it. C.L.R James considers it an oppertune time to print and 
                    discusses publicity with the COlonial Office, he states he will write an article and send it
                    to Mr Kingsley Martin alongside a draft to Leonard Woolf.
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1932-11-15">
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <persName> Leonard Woolf </persName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            3 Mircrth St <lb/>
                            Nelson <lb/>
                            Luncs <lb/>
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName key= "Q703935">Mr Woolf</persName>,
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    Thanks extremely <lb/>
                    for your kind letter. I was <lb/>
                    glad that you like the book. <lb/>
                    I shall prepare a <lb/>
                    pamphlet of 10,000 words <lb/>
                    and sincerely hope you <lb/>
                    will see your way to <lb/>
                    publish it. The fact that <lb/>
                    the commission is actually <lb/>
                    taking evidence now and <lb/>
                    will do so until March <lb/>
                    next year marks the <lb/>
                    present time opportune. I <pb/>
                    do not know if I am <lb/>
                    wrong in thinking that <lb/>
                    a little publicity in <lb/>
                    the right quantity on this <lb/>
                    side would have some <lb/>
                    weight with the com- <lb/>
                    missioners and the <lb/>
                    Colonial Office. <lb/>
                    I shall prepare a short <lb/>
                    article and send it <lb/>
                    to <persName key= "Q6413326">Mr. Kingsley Martin</persName> ; and <lb/>
                    as soon as it is typed <lb/>
                    I shall send you a <lb/>
                    copy of the draft
                    compilation.
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        yours sincerely <lb/>
                    </salute>
                    <persName key= "Q773828">C.L.R.James</persName>
                    <signed/>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
